# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# --- COMMIT MESSAGE GUIDELINES ---
#
# Format follows the Conventional Commits spec (https://www.conventionalcommits.org/).
#
# Subject line:
#   - <type>: one of feat, fix, chore, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, revert
#   - <scope> (optional): area of the codebase, e.g. web, contracts, deploy
#   - <subject>: short imperative description, no trailing period, lowercase preferred
#   - Keep the whole subject under ~72 characters
#   - Append "!" before the colon (or add a "BREAKING CHANGE:" footer) for breaking changes
#
# Body (optional):
#   - Wrap at ~72 characters
#   - Explain the *why* of the change, not the *what*
#
# Footer (optional):
#   - Reference issues:        Closes #123
#   - Mark breaking changes:   BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
#
# Examples:
#   feat(web): add wallet connect button
#   fix(contracts): handle zero-address transfer revert
#   docs: clarify deploy script options
#   refactor(web)!: drop legacy svelte store API
